[normal]Joint written evidence submitted by Bob Ward and Naomi Hicks (CLC041)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The Grantham Research Institute on Climate Change and the Environment at the London School of 
[normal]Economics and Political Science,
[normal] is a 
[normal]research centre, chaired by Nicholas 
[normal]Stern
[normal], which brings together international expertise on economics, finance, geography, international development and political economy.
[normal] Bob Ward is the Policy and Communications Director. Naomi Hicks is the Institute’s Public Communications Manager. 
[normal]The Insti
[normal]tute is funded by the Grantham F
[normal]oundation for the Protection of the Environment and the Global Green Growth Institute. The work of the Institute is integrated with the activities of the Centre for Climate Change Economics and Policy, which is hosted by the London School of Economics 
[normal]and Political Science 
[normal]and the University of Leeds, and funded by the UK Economic and Social Research Council and Munich Re.
